OL,3,CChildren in England waiting years for
OL,4,Cautism and cerebral palsy diagnoses
OL,6,FChildren referred for Down's Syndrome
OL,7,Fwaited the longest between referral
OL,8,Fand a first appointment through
OL,9,Fcommunity health services, at an
OL,10,Faverage of around two years and seven
OL,11,Fmonths.
OL,13,FThere were waits of more than 1,000
OL,14,Fdays for children with intellectual
OL,15,Fdisorders such as those which affect
OL,16,Ftheir learning, judgment, reasoning or
OL,17,Fproblem-solving abilities, while those
OL,18,Fwith tic disorders, including
OL,19,FTourette's syndrome had waits of more
OL,20,Fthan 800 days to get a diagnosis.
