OL,3,CChildren in England waiting years for
OL,4,Cautism and cerebral palsy diagnoses
OL,6,FDiagnosis for any neurodevelopmental
OL,7,Fcondition through community services
OL,8,Fsaw an average wait of two years and
OL,9,Fthree months, with four in 10 children
OL,10,F(41%, or 14,800) waiting longer than
OL,11,Ftwo years for their diagnosis across
OL,12,Fboth services.
OL,14,FOf these, almost a fifth (17% or 6,150
OL,15,Fchildren) waited more than four years,
OL,16,Fthe commissioner said.
